[Patient] Can you tell me how much water I should be drinking each day? 
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for around 8 cups of water a day, but adjust based on your doctor's advice. 
[Patient] Is it okay to drink other beverages like tea or juice instead of water? 
[Healthcare Educator] Water is the best choice, but you can include some tea or juice in moderation. 
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake throughout the day? 
[Healthcare Educator] Try using a smartphone app or keeping a written log to monitor your fluid intake. 
[Patient] What happens if I drink too much water or fluids? 
[Healthcare Educator] Drinking too much can lead to fluid overload, causing swelling and breathing difficulties. 
[Patient] How can I stay motivated to keep track of my fluid intake daily? 
[Healthcare Educator] Set reminders on your phone, involve a family member, or use a reward system for motivation.